   <tr valign=top><td height="200"><b><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2" color=black>
<div class=profile>If there is any well known name amongst the locations of Sonic, South Island would most certainly be it.  It houses the classic Sonic atmosphere with sparkling waters and checkered hill sides.  Though it has never been confirmed whether or not this is Sonic's true home (though in all honesty, does Sonic really have a "home"?), it is home to an assorment of different little animals including Flicky, Ricky, Pocky, Picky, Cucky, Pecky and Rocky.  It is home to probably more zones than any other location, and is also home to the biggest, and probably most over explored zone, the Green Hill Zone.

<p>Perhaps the strangest quirk about the island is it's cirular rotation in the ocean.  It was because of this rotation, along with the island's unique shape, that the mystical Chaos Emeralds drifted endlessly through a torison between the rifts of time and space.  That is until Dr. Eggman discovered their secret, and attempted to obtain them by building his base, the Scrap Brain Zone, in the exact same shape as the island, probably in hopes that the dimension would open within the base, handing the Emeralds, straight over to him (even though we all know he can do better than that).

<p>One last note would be that in Sonic & Tails, it was said that the island required the Chaos Emeralds to support its vitality, otherwise it would sink into the ocean.  It's hard to say whether this is true, but because the Chaos Emeralds have long since been seperated from South Island, it can probably be disregraded.

